<subSubSection id="AB4FEF781CE74679A0547A8610B3C721" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A2A8FB4710E247B073225ACE5D79BB43" pageNumber="269">
diagnosis A medium-sized reddish brown (major) or brownish yellow (minor) member of the 
<taxonomicName id="BC7629BD32DBDB96CE35BAEC45F68CE8" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group distinguished as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B421161CA4199D9E4B8CBBA4DF1946A3" type="description">
<paragraph id="D871AC3712CEAFC5446CAA1E3D00219B" pageNumber="269">Major: head subquadrate; propodeal spine moderately long and suberect; postpetiolar node from above roughly trapezoidal; mesonotal convexity prominent and symmetrical in shape in both side and dorsal-oblique views; rugoreticulum extends as a broad band from the eye to the circular carinulae of the antennal fossa; frontal lobes completely covered by longitudinal carinulae; carinulae mesad to the eye reach halfway between the eye and the occipital border.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1E6339395477CADC5F448190E8C03DE" pageNumber="269">
Minor: occiput narrow, with nuchal collar; humerus smoothly rounded in dorsal-oblique view. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CBD1A4EDF01B86671CF9C70480767BD6" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181716" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole aenescens Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole aenescens Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">aenescens</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2935AB211067B2DD522FF6F950EBC9EA" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181717" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole alienata Borgmeier" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole alienata Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alienata">alienata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AE65F079C308C6DC2F826A9A3CA4C93A" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181664" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chrysops Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chrysops Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysops">chrysops</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6870995DF1DC00CDA7C690D52E8EC886" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33685" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cordiceps Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cordiceps Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiceps">cordiceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5B480D67F0020405B9A5058DDAEAA433" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33704" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole dentata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole dentata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentata">dentata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FB26FDF9E2485C126C79A22AEFAB27B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181727" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole dione Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole dione Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dione">dione</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59F768976FC56CC6984FD6E23E3052B9" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33720" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole eidmanni Menozzi" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole eidmanni Menozzi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eidmanni">eidmanni</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E25B1E2B9A8B54A00990F65C95D930E0" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181805" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole midas Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole midas Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="midas">midas</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="B85C82A4F896A58A92099B94205A8E12" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33896" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole nitidula Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole nitidula Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidula">nitidula</taxonomicName>
, differing in many details as described and illustrated. measurements (mm) Syntype major: HW 1.94 (Cafayate, Argentina, major has HW 1.54), HL 2.08, SL 1.12, EL 0.32, PW 0.96. Minor (Cafayate): HW 0.56, HL 0.80, SL 1.10, EL 0.16, PW 0.38.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9A9538766D9B1F7E7A9C42500E51F5A" pageNumber="269">Color Major: body mostly light reddish brown; terminal gastral segments medium reddish brown. Minor: concolorous brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55E96E3DA8718AC1324FB73910B85392" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B84359E718097AFC0995F26EE6DF1160" pageNumber="269">range Uruguay, and widespread through Argentina, from Jujuy and Santa Fe in the north to Rio Negro in the south.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1FA42790B03B5C68B5DC55A093773E62" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="3ED109CA33F8358F0D9D0E92F77DA07A" pageNumber="269">
biology Bruch (1916) describes 
<taxonomicName id="BD3A44A87FF5D28387FF057AE215EA3C" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33614" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole bergi Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole bergi Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergi">bergi</taxonomicName>
as an abundant, widespread species in Argentina. It builds conspicuous soil nests, each with a single entrance hole 2-3 cm in diameter, often surrounded by a crater or partially by a semicircle of excavated soil as much as 25 cm in diameter. A single gallery descends to a succession of 5 to 10 roughly ellipsoidal chambers, each spaced about equally apart, and reaching a depth of 40-60 cm. The colonies are aggressive, with a high proportion of majors, and exclusively insectivorous. They readily attack other colonies of their own and other ant species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
